    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-15T02:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-15T02:30:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">689.90D/5–1551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jandrey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-15T12:00:00+04:30"
                            >May 15, 1951—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>353. Pass CSGID. Under Secretary Fon Off<note n="1" xml:id="d334fn1">Abdul Samad
                        Khan, First Undersecretary of the Royal Afghan Ministry of Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> called Brit, Indian, Sov and Amer Embassies today to inform
                    them that 5,000 regular <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> troops composed of
                    army and militia are being brought up to Baqi post area on Baluchistan border
                    with tanks, guns and ammunition. Under Secretary did not indicate that <gloss
                        target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> troops had as yet attacked Afghans. Press has
                    reported capture of 25 more <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> troops in border
                    area four or five days ago.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> Emb believes Afghan Govt’s intention is to
                    publicize threatened aggression in order win support in case of border
                    disturbance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jandrey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
